<br>
For a period of time after our 1st dd was born, we used our tithing money for other things for about a year (blame it on a momentary lack of faith, I guess) but we got so far in debt in that year, that it took us almost 4 years after we started paying our tithing again to get out of those debts.<br>
<br>
You show those sad pictures.... I served my mission in Costa Rica in some very poor areas.  I saw peoples lives change for the better after they accepted the gospel and lived the law of Tithing.  In all my years being in the church I have never once heard ANYONE say you know I paid my tithing and things have really just gotten worse, but I hear all the time.  We paid our tithing and these are the blessings we have received....<br>
<br>
Maybe the blessing is being prompted to buy extra meat one shopping trip or maybe it is finding a job right away after loosing another, maybe its an old beat up car getting better gas mileage than it should physically be capable of.  Myabe it is the Bishop being impressed to come over to their house and talk to them when things were getting tight and he offers help..All sorts of ways for simple blessings.<br>
<br>
I know that God doesnt need my money, but he asks for my obedience and promises blessings if I do.   I also know that no one is getting rich off of it.  We have a lay ministry.  The money builds temples and churches and helps cover the costs of missions and humanitarian efforts. It pays for 3 Universities and some church owned elementry and high schools in some less fortunate countries.  It covers the cost of maintaining all the buildings lights power heat etc.  The LDS is a &quot;wealthy church&quot; but its money is turned right around and blesses the lives of church members and needy people across the world.  We even have a perpetual education fund, where  young people who are less fortunate or in  3rd world countries can get college or technical training to better there lives.<br>
<br>
<br>
Bad things still happen to good people: cancer, death of a spouse, problems with the economy, but I know what I have experienced and from my experience I know that paying my tithing and putting God first only blesses my life.  I know this will be hard for the skeptic to believe, but the simple fact is I have done it both ways and  I know from my experience that &quot;it works&quot;   I challenged my 16-18 yo in sunday school to give it a 6 month trial and see for themselves.  I havent had anyone come back to me telling me they tried it and were not blessed for it.<br>
<br>
