<br>
Bishops arent paid. Stake Presdients arent paid.  General Authorities have their travel expenses paid  for conferences all over the world, but most the time they stay in the homes of members where ever they are going to reduce costs.   I *think* if they dont have enough money on their own to live when they are called  they are given some living allowances But a good deal are older and already have retirement or other income -- The one GA I personally know is a retired Lawyer and isnt lacking for money.  He doesnt need any living allowances.   <br>
<br>
If a person wants to donate to the Humanitarian fund or the perpetual education fund you can do that directly, all of the money is used for those purposes.  Each ward and Stake and all the general accounts are audited annually the general ones are done by an outside accounting firm. - Shirene<br>
